illness became seen primarily
as a physical phenomenon,

00:14:06.830 --> 00:14:10.416 align:middle line:90%
no longer involving the soul.

00:14:10.416 --> 00:14:14.320 align:middle line:84%
The mentally ill were typically
viewed more as wild animals,

00:14:14.320 --> 00:14:16.980 align:middle line:84%
and harsh treatments
and restraints,

00:14:16.980 --> 00:14:21.150 align:middle line:84%
similar to Medieval times,
were seen as therapeutic.

00:14:21.150 --> 00:14:24.420 align:middle line:10%
>>In England, people used
to go by a famous asylum

00:14:24.420 --> 00:14:27.500 align:middle line:10%
called Bedlam that had
been there for centuries,

00:14:27.500 --> 00:14:32.510 align:middle line:10%
looking in through the gates at
the wild, psychotic, peculiar

00:14:32.510 --> 00:14:34.470 align:middle line:10%
mental patients.

00:14:34.470 --> 00:14:37.320 align:middle line:84%
>>German psychiatrist
Emil Kraepelin,

00:14:37.320 --> 00:14:40.760 align:middle line:84%
considered the founder of
modern scientific psychiatry,

00:14:40.760 --> 00:14:44.240 align:middle line:84%
spoke out against this
inhumane treatment.

00:14:44.240 --> 00:14:47.430 align:middle line:84%
He believed the chief origin
of psychiatric disease

00:14:47.430 --> 00:14:49.260 align:middle line:90%
to be biological.

00:14:49.260 --> 00:14:51.460 align:middle line:84%
And by identifying
specific disorders,

00:14:51.460 --> 00:14:53.400 align:middle line:84%
the progression
of mental illness

00:14:53.400 --> 00:14:55.415 align:middle line:90%
can be predicted and treated.

00:14:55.415 --> 00:14:58.350 align:middle line:84%
And his theories
dominated psychiatry

00:14:58.350 --> 00:15:01.560 align:middle line:90%
at the turn of the 20th century.

00:15:01.560 --> 00:15:05.670 align:middle line:84%
>>Perhaps in response
to this overemphasis

00:15:05.670 --> 00:15:10.060 align:middle line:84%
on biological factors,
the early 20th century

00:15:10.060 --> 00:15:14.240 align:middle line:84%
saw three great pioneers
within psychiatry.

00:15:14.240 --> 00:15:17.970 align:middle line:84%
They recognized that, many
times, diseases of the body

00:15:17.970 --> 00:15:22.440 align:middle line:84%
actually have their origin
in conflicts and fears based

00:15:22.440 --> 00:15:25.850 align:middle line:84%
in the mind, that you couldn't
actually treat mind and body as

00:15:25.850 --> 00:15:28.990 align:middle line:84%
though they were separate
from one another.

00:15:28.990 --> 00:15:31.720 align:middle line:84%
>>As a result, early
psychiatry split

00:15:31.720 --> 00:15:36.060 align:middle line:84%
into two competing traditions,
one emphasizing thoughts,

00:15:36.060 --> 00:15:39.430 align:middle line:84%
emotions, and dreams as
the keys to the healing

00:15:39.430 --> 00:15:42.270 align:middle line:84%
of mental disorders,
and another that

00:15:42.270 --> 00:15:44.620 align:middle line:84%
looked for clues
to these disorders

00:15:44.620 --> 00:15:46.260 align:middle line:90%
in the tissues of the brain.

00:15:46.260 --> 00:15:49.300 align:middle line:90%


00:15:49.300 --> 00:15:52.500 align:middle line:84%
Over the course of 50
years, many offshoots

00:15:52.500 --> 00:15:55.000 align:middle line:84%
of Freud's initial
concepts formed,

00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:57.540 align:middle line:84%
so many that it became
difficult for the movement

00:15:57.540 --> 00:15:59.800 align:middle line:84%
to philosophically
hold together.

00:15:59.800 --> 00:16:01.330 align:middle line:10%
Disagreement about
which treatments

00:16:01.330 --> 00:16:03.800 align:middle line:10%
matched which symptoms,
and controversy

00:16:03.800 --> 00:16:07.730 align:middle line:10%
of the overall effectiveness of
treatment stalled the movement.

00:16:07.730 --> 00:16:10.800 align:middle line:84%
And this laid the groundwork
for the course psychiatry

00:16:10.800 --> 00:16:13.680 align:middle line:90%
would take to present day.

00:16:13.680 --> 00:16:15.840 align:middle line:84%
>>In the second half
of the 20th century,

00:16:15.840 --> 00:16:18.290 align:middle line:84%
we witnessed another
major revolution

00:16:18.290 --> 00:16:20.130 align:middle line:90%
within the field of psychiatry.

00:16:20.130 --> 00:16:23.000 align:middle line:84%
For the first time
ever, medications

00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:24.950 align:middle line:84%
were discovered
that could treat,

00:16:24.950 --> 00:16:27.440 align:middle line:84%
or at least to some
extent reverse,

00:16:27.440 --> 00:16:31.700 align:middle line:84%
some of the symptoms of
major psychiatric illness.

00:16:31.700 --> 00:16:34.320 align:middle line:84%
The discovery of these
medication treatments

00:16:34.320 --> 00:16:37.300 align:middle line:84%
once again swung
the pendulum back

00:16:37.300 --> 00:16:39.050 align:middle line:90%
towards a biological emphasis.

00:16:39.050 --> 00:16:44.010 align:middle line:90%


00:16:44.010 --> 00:16:48.360 align:middle line:84%
>>Unlike the unbroken 5,000-year
tradition of the holistic

00:16:48.360 --> 00:16:52.270 align:middle line:90%
practice of Ayurvedic medicine.

00:16:52.270 --> 00:16:53.920 align:middle line:10%
The history of
Western medicine has

00:16:53.920 --> 00:16:57.010 align:middle line:10%
seen an ongoing struggle
for the influence--

00:16:57.010 --> 00:17:00.600 align:middle line:10%
and often control--
between examining the mind,

00:17:00.600 --> 00:17:04.670 align:middle line:10%
examining the body, and
examining the soul in order

00:17:04.670 --> 00:17:08.030 align:middle line:10%
to diagnose and heal.

00:17:08.030 --> 00:17:11.230 align:middle line:10%
The question is, are
we now on the verge

00:17:11.230 --> 00:17:13.099 align:middle line:10%
of moving towards
a new paradigm?

00:17:13.099 --> 00:17:19.087 align:middle line:90%


00:17:19.087 --> 00:17:21.083 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTER]

00:17:21.083 --> 00:17:24.079 align:middle line:90%


00:17:24.079 --> 00:17:25.730 align:middle line:84%
>>I feel so out of
