00:17:58.145 --> 00:17:59.250 align:middle line:10%
I have no future.

00:17:59.250 --> 00:18:02.270 align:middle line:84%
>>The challenges that our
younger generation now face

00:18:02.270 --> 00:18:05.010 align:middle line:84%
have created a surge in
mental health issues,

00:18:05.010 --> 00:18:07.120 align:middle line:84%
and Western psychiatry
is grappling

00:18:07.120 --> 00:18:09.495 align:middle line:84%
with the most effective way
to address this epidemic.

00:18:09.495 --> 00:18:15.740 align:middle line:90%


00:18:15.740 --> 00:18:18.590 align:middle line:84%
>>Making a psychiatric diagnosis
can be quite challenging.

00:18:18.590 --> 00:18:21.210 align:middle line:90%


00:18:21.210 --> 00:18:23.720 align:middle line:84%
Unlike other
medical specialties,

00:18:23.720 --> 00:18:26.615 align:middle line:84%
there's no particular
blood test or scans

00:18:26.615 --> 00:18:32.110 align:middle line:84%
or x-rays which can make
a definitive diagnosis.

00:18:32.110 --> 00:18:34.800 align:middle line:84%
The cornerstone of a
psychiatric diagnosis

00:18:34.800 --> 00:18:37.990 align:middle line:84%
really is the
clinical interview.

00:18:37.990 --> 00:18:41.500 align:middle line:84%
I'll often begin by asking
the patient how their mood has

00:18:41.500 --> 00:18:44.680 align:middle line:84%
been, how their sleeping
