00:19:21.600 --> 00:19:24.320 align:middle line:84%
abuse, which is
critical in taking

00:19:24.320 --> 00:19:27.440 align:middle line:84%
a history on any
psychiatric patient.

00:19:27.440 --> 00:19:29.300 align:middle line:84%
These two problems
are so prevalent.

00:19:29.300 --> 00:19:32.650 align:middle line:90%


00:19:32.650 --> 00:19:35.120 align:middle line:84%
>>I'll also review
their medical records

00:19:35.120 --> 00:19:37.380 align:middle line:84%
to see what other types
of health problems

00:19:37.380 --> 00:19:40.140 align:middle line:84%
they may have encountered,
since this may also

00:19:40.140 --> 00:19:43.890 align:middle line:90%
impact their emotional wellness.

00:19:43.890 --> 00:19:45.890 align:middle line:90%
>>I want to see an EKG.

00:19:45.890 --> 00:19:49.350 align:middle line:84%
I want to see a
biochemical profile

00:19:49.350 --> 00:19:52.120 align:middle line:90%
and any neurologic workup.

00:19:52.120 --> 00:19:54.700 align:middle line:84%
The reason that we
are so concerned

00:19:54.700 --> 00:19:58.890 align:middle line:84%
about the medical
condition-- there

00:19:58.890 --> 00:20:02.780 align:middle line:84%
are many medical illnesses
that are mimicked

00:20:02.780 --> 00:20:05.590 align:middle line:84%
by psychiatric illness,
and vice versa.

00:20:05.590 --> 00:20:08.610 align:middle line:84%
